did.abstract: The Neuman Library, 1974-2013 Records document the careers and initiatives of Francis Weeks and Gay Carter who were librarians at the University of Houston-Clear Lake Neuman Library.

bioghist.head: Administrative History
bioghist.p: Frances Weeks began working at Neumann Library on March 1, 1996 and served as Coordinator of Access Services, supervising both the interlibrary loan and circulation departments. During her time here, she donated a complete collection of Newbery Medal award winning books to the Curriculum Library. She also was instrumental in the formation of the UHCL Veterans Scholarship Endowment, which she, along with others, helped fund. She was active in the UHCL Veteran's Day Celebrations, The President's Cabinet, and was part of the charter class of Leaders in Action. She retired from the University on January 2, 2014 after 17.5 years of employment.

Gay Carter served as a charter reference librarian from the time the University opened its doors in 1974. In 1980, she began supervising Neumann Library's federal depository and Texas state depository collections. She was active in the Government Documents Round Table of the Texas Library Association, serving as both chair-elect and chair. Gay has been involved for many years in genealogical research and has been a featured speaker, presenter, and writer for several genealogical organizations. She retired from the University in May, 2013.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents of the Records
scopecontent.p: These are records which were generated or collected by librarians Frances Weeks and Gay Carter during their years at Neumann Library. Included are records relating to the daily processes of running the library, library meeting minutes, policies, memos, fiscal files, library and university events, library brochures and publications, staff information, and general subject files. Both Gay and Frances also served on numerous UHCL Shared Governance Committees and those files are contained herein.
The last three folders of box twelve are closed due to privacy issues.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: These files belonged to librarians Frances Weeks and Gay Carter and were donated to the Archives upon their retirement from Neumann Library. Frances' files were donated over the course of several weeks during September and October, 2013. Gay's vertical file records were transferred to the archives in June, 2013 by librarian Martha Steele. This collection is made up of their combined donations
